&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a key growth accelerator, A11 partners with Europe’s most ambitious startups and scaleups, corporates and SMBs to connect them with top-tier talent ready to make an impact.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for an AI Product Lead (m/f/d) to own one of the most technically ambitious and commercially consequential AI initiatives in European B2B. Our partner company is a leading B2B mobility and payment solutions provider active in 50+ countries, with around 2,700 employees and €19 billion in transaction volume. As the business enters its next phase, it is investing heavily in data and AI to strengthen its market position at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;You will own the full Sales Models portfolio - Next Best Action, Churn, Customer Lifetime Value, and adjacent use cases - and lead a cross-functional team of Data Scientists and Engineers to deliver it. You set the roadmap, the technical standard, and the business case. You translate model outputs into decisions that reach C-level, and field reality into model improvements. This is not a coordination role. You define what gets built, in which order, and why.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you’ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;Own the product roadmap for the Sales Models portfolio: NBA engine, Churn integration, CLV modeling, and adjacent use cases such as cross-/upsell logic and share-of-wallet estimation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;Lead a cross-functional team of 3-5 Data Scientists and 1-2 Engineers with full functional authority: technical direction, prioritization, sprint cadence, quality gates, and delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;Drive integration of sales models into operative systems (Dynamics 365, Power BI) and own the feedback loop between field sales, CRM data, and model iteration - turning market signals into systematic improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;Translate GTM requirements into model specifications and model constraints into business-actionable trade-offs for senior leadership, while building the governance infrastructure that makes the portfolio sustainable at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Profile:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;5-7 years at the intersection of Data Science, AI Product Management, and Engineering, ideally combining two of: a top-tier consultancy data science practice, a Lead Data Scientist role with team responsibility, or an AI/ML PM role at a scale-up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;Technically deep (Python, SQL, ML frameworks, cloud data infrastructure) and able to lead Data Scientists credibly: setting direction on model architecture, reviewing feature engineering choices, and stepping into the code when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;You think in business cases and revenue impact, not just model accuracy - and can communicate trade-offs clearly to both a CCO and a Data Scientist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;Fluent in German and English; willingness to travel within Europe 1-2 times per month&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
