&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;7e1ye6&quot; data-start=&quot;1265&quot; data-end=&quot;1360&quot;&gt;Act as the first point of contact for employee questions ab

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a key growth accelerator, A11 partners with Europe’s most ambitious startups and scaleups, corporates and SMBs to connect them with top-tier talent ready to make an impact.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Principal Data Scientist (m/f/d) &lt;/strong&gt;in Credit &amp;amp; Risk Management to take ownership of the Smart Risk engine at the core of one of Europe’s leading B2B mobility and payment platforms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our partner company serves customers across more than 50 countries. Built on over 90 years of continuous growth and innovation, the company has evolved into a market-leading platform with around 2,700 employees, processing €19 billion in transaction volume. As the business enters its next phase of development, it is investing heavily in data, AI, and technology-enabled commercial excellence to strengthen its market position and unlock new opportunities at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will own the Smart Risk Engine end to end. From feature strategy and model training to calibration, backtesting, drift monitoring, and explainability. This is a hands-on role, which means you will design data-driven use cases such as early-warning systems, loss databases, limit and exposure steering, and portfolio insights that directly shape how credit risk is managed across the platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With direct exposure to senior decision makers, real influence over how risk is quantified and managed at scale, this role offers a rare opportunity to shape a business critical capability from the inside.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you’ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take full ownership of data-driven analyses, independently deriving actionable recommendations to maximise business value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and apply advanced statistical methods (regression models, time series analyses, ML/AI algorithms) and translate results into clear, compelling business insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and maintain robust end-to-end ML pipelines (data, features, models, scoring), including testing, versioning, documentation, and MLOps standards such as CI/CD, model registry, monitoring, data-quality checks, and incident handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with stakeholders and management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the SmartRisk Engine within Credit &amp;amp; Risk Management: feature strategy, training/retraining, calibration, backtesting, drift monitoring, and explainability via SHAP/Reason Codes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build data-driven use cases such as loss databases, early-warning systems, limit/exposure steering, clustering, and portfolio insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop new cloud-based Data Science solutions, primarily in Python and SQL, to drive measurable business value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally, you bring knowledge in credit risk (e.g., PD, EAD, LGD, rating, IFRS 9/ECL) and experience with SAP and Power BI&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and guide other Data Scientists, encourage innovative thinking, and actively support the team&#39;s professional growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Profile:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-8 years of experience in Data Science and Machine Learning, confidently applying statistical methods, regression models, time series analyses, classical ML, and modern AI algorithms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly proficient in Python and SQL, independently developing value-adding, cloud-based solutions, including Generative AI use cases such as LLMs, RAG systems, and &quot;talk-to-your-data&quot; interfaces (AI agents or chat interfaces)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record building robust end-to-end ML pipelines and maintaining MLOps standards (CI/CD, model registry, monitoring, quality checks)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on ownership of risk mod

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a key growth accelerator, A11 partners with Europe’s most ambitious startups and scaleups, corporates and SMBs to connect them with top-tier talent ready to make an impact.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Procurement Manager (m/f/d) &lt;/strong&gt;to&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;command a multi-million euro spend to secure the partnerships that underpin our client&#39;s international expansion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Procurement Manager, you&#39;ll blend commercial savvy with a data-first mindset to transform market volatility into a competitive advantage for the entire organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join the A11 Ecosystem – &lt;/strong&gt;A next-generation supply chain platform, the company is redefining how one of the world’s largest industries sources, distributes, and finances materials. Engineered to unlock the full potential of global trade, it harnesses agentic AI and workflow automation to provide seamless, high-efficiency access to premium materials at scale. Since its commercial rollout, the platform has fueled exponential growth, optimizing procurement for thousands of businesses while setting new benchmarks for speed, transparency, and efficiency. Its competitive edge lies in full digitization and AI-driven supply chain management automation, eliminating inefficiencies and creating a direct, intelligent bridge between suppliers and buyers. With a team of 80+ FTEs across Europe (Berlin HQ), China, and India, the company is rapidly scaling toward profitability, driving triple-digit million GMV, and setting new industry standards in autonomous, AI-powered supply chain orchestration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you’ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, engage, and acquire suppliers across Europe and worldwide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead negotiations for pricing, payment terms, and contracts of 1M+ procurement spend&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building strong commercial relationships that fuel company growth and ensure reliable supply&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute strategic plans to drive operational growth and efficiency, aligning with the company’s global objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Sales and operational teams to solve issues, improve operational processes that leverage automation and data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze performance data, track key KPIs, and deliver actionable insights to optimize end-to-end supply chain operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze market trends, supplier capabilities, and pricing structures and adjust strategy accordingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify cost-saving opportunities and drive continuous improvement initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support long-term sourcing plans and risk mitigation strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve supplier-related issues including quality, delivery, or compliance concerns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Profile:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You hold a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Business, Supply Chain Management or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are experienced in the field of procurement sourcing, supply chain contracting and eager to take on responsibility in a fast-scaling, tech-driven environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have strong analytical and negotiation skills, and can clearly articulate complex subjects with confidence and precision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You bring a hands-on mentality – you take ownership, solve problems independently, and thrive in dynamic settings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are motivated by technology-driven transformation and curious about how AI can reshape global supply chains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full business proficiency in German (preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that this position is based onsite in &lt;strong&gt;Berlin&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp

&lt;p class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;A11 ist der ausführende Wachstumstreiber hinter Europas führenden Tech-Unicorns wie Trade Republic, Sennder und Kry. Wir sind ein SWAT-Team für Business Performance mit Expertise in Marketing, Sales, Data, Tech und People Ops. Mit mehr als 100 internationalen Expert:innen gehen wir komplexe Herausforderungen in Business und Technologie gezielt an. Ob Produkteinführungen in Rekordzeit oder die Transformation ganzer Geschäftsmodelle – wir liefern messbaren Impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;Die Position&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bereit zum Aufbauen und Skalieren? Bei A11 glauben wir, dass Umsetzung wichtiger ist als Theorie. Wir suchen eine/n engagierte/n Product Manager (m/w/d), um Teil unseres Product-Teams zu werden und durch die Entwicklung von Ergebnissen, Wandel voranzutreiben und messbare Resultate zu erzielen. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wir suchen jemanden, der gemeinsam mit uns Produkte bei unseren Partnern und in unserem Ökosystem entwickelt, iteriert und vorantreibt. Wenn du motiviert bist, echten Einfluss zu nehmen und Resultate zu liefern, möchten wir dich kennenlernen!&lt;/p&gt;
